G/T Lover, Writer, Multiple Fandoms Lover, Uses She/Her, bisexual
Header by stuff-from-the-void-matron

summary: Unknown Satisfaction
body:
Unknown Satisfaction

The next time (former friend) and (former friend’s boyfriend) saw (Y/N), they honestly weren’t expecting her to already be with someone. They weren’t even looking. What got their attention was hearing her sing.

When they turned, they saw her being twirled by a man that looked decently well off. He was tall, black hair that had a medium fringe on the right side but short all around. He had some strange makeup on his face, a streak of blue-purple under each eye. Other than that, he was a fairly attractive man.

He wore near completely from the tight black denim jeans to the black leather jacket. The only splash of color on him was a purple Mew shirt.

What he wore was very similar to what (Y/N) had on; black skinny jeans, black denim jacket, and a black shirt with a blue figure on the front. She had her hair differently from how they were used to seeing it. Then again, before, (Former friend) and (Former friend’s boyfriend) knew (Y/N) wasn’t that confident in having their her hair as it was naturally. Yet here she was, natural (your natural hairstyle). The only alteration was how she had it dyed (favorite color) at the ends.

“Come to the land of the lost and lonely

Don’t be afraid, we’ll be one big family

Of freaks like you and me

I know a place where the bruised and broken

Live like the kings and the queens of tragedy

Just freaks like you and me

We are the freaks”

They heard her sing, smiling broadly when the man pulled her to his side, smiling back at her, his dimples showing. As much as they tried to look away, they couldn’t help but keep glancing back at the two.

It looked like she acted the same as when she was with them; overly affectionate, humming or singing some song, being childish.

When she kissed the man on the cheek, it wasn’t surprising since she did the same to (former friend) a few times on the cheek before. Though it changed as they watched the man smile down at her with adoration.

He leaned down to rest his forehead against hers, nuzzling her cheek for a moment, seemingly murmuring something that they couldn’t hear but made her grin even broader, wrapping her arms around his neck.

They were surprised to see her to kiss him, recalling times when she would be too anxious or shy to instigate anything.

The two pulled apart when they heard the train. The couple turned at the sight of the train pulling up, quick to hurry on, never letting go of each other’s hand as they went up the platform, just making it inside the train before the doors shut.

That was that last time they saw (Y/N) and the mysterious man. You never know if you will; it was a small town.

-
